x4freetext: Experiment was conducted at the
University of Notre Dames` Nuclear Science Laboratory.
Neutrons were detected using 4 in. diameter x
6 in. deep (4" x 6") and 2 in. diameter x 2 in. deep
(2" x 2") EJ315 detectors. The entrance windows of
the 4" x 6" detectors were located at a radius of 1.0
m and those of the 2" x 2" detectors at 50 cm with
respect to the central target position.
Two methods were used to determine cross sections.
First was deuteron-recoil peak fitting from the light
spectra and the second was fitting peaks in an unfolded
neutron-energy spectrum. For ground state cross section
determination the simpler case of ground-state deuteron
recoil peak was used.
